All drugs have side effects. That´s part of the development process - thoroughly test the side effects and evaluate if the drug is not causing more harm than good. Second point: these drugs are ultimately tested on people - ordinary people, who report if they felt some side effects. Due to the financial incentive they often report side effects such as dizziness, headache etc. even when they are not feeling any. Obviously - they are getting paid for reporting side effects, not just taking the pill. That combined means that when you focus on the side effects part of the information, you will find a long list of almost anything. And then there is the other possibility - just taking a joint.
